Defining the Registration and optimization functions

In [0]:
# Register function using cv2
import cv2
from scipy.optimize import minimize

def register(scale,angle,move_x,move_y,interpolate,image):
    
    # IF interpolate ==1 then linear else nearest neighbor
    
    [rows,cols]=np.shape(image)
    out = cv2.getRotationMatrix2D((rows/2,cols/2), angle, scale)
    if(interpolate==1):
        out = cv2.warpAffine(image,out,(rows,cols),flags=cv2.INTER_LINEAR)
    else:
        out = cv2.warpAffine(image,out,(rows,cols),flags=cv2.INTER_NEAREST)
    
    translation_matrix = np.float32([ [1,0,move_x], [0,1,move_y] ])
    out = cv2.warpAffine(out, translation_matrix, (cols, rows))
    
    return [out,np.shape(out)]

def loss(param,interpolate,images):
    [fix,moving]=images
    [scale,angle,move_x,move_y]=param
    
    #First calculate the moving image
    
    [out,[rows,cols]]=register(scale,angle,move_x,move_y,interpolate,moving)
    
    loss_sum=0
    for i in range(rows):
        for j in range(cols):
            loss_sum=loss_sum + (fix[i,j] - out[i,j])**2
    
    return loss_sum


def optimize(param,interpolate,images):
    x0=param
    res=minimize(loss,x0,args=(interpolate,images,),method='nelder-mead')
    
    [scale,angle,move_x,move_y]=res.x
    [fix,moving]=images
    [out,shape]=register(scale,angle,move_x,move_y,interpolate,moving)
    return [res.x,out]

Question 5: Jaccard Index¶

In [0]:
def jaccard(img1,img2,label):
    [rows,cols]=np.shape(img1)
    
    union=0
    inter=0
    
    for i in range(rows):
        for j in range(cols):
            if(img1[i,j]==label and img2[i,j]==label):
                inter=inter+1
            if(img1[i,j]==label or img2[i,j]==label):
                union=union+1
    
    return inter/union

# Register function using cv2
import cv2
from scipy.optimize import minimize

def register_comp(scale,angle,move_x,move_y,interpolate,image):
    
    # IF interpolate ==1 then linear else nearest neighbor
    
    [rows,cols]=np.shape(image)
    out = cv2.getRotationMatrix2D((rows/2,cols/2), angle, scale)
    if(interpolate==1):
        out = cv2.warpAffine(image,out,(rows,cols),flags=cv2.INTER_LINEAR)
    else:
        out = cv2.warpAffine(image,out,(rows,cols),flags=cv2.INTER_NEAREST)
    
    translation_matrix = np.float32([ [1,0,move_x], [0,1,move_y] ])
    out = cv2.warpAffine(out, translation_matrix, (cols, rows))
    #out = cv2.logPolar(out, (127,127),log,cv2.WARP_FILL_OUTLIERS)
    
    return [out,np.shape(out)]

def loss_comp(param,interpolate,images):
    [fix,moving]=images
    [scale,angle,move_x,move_y]=param
    
    #First calculate the moving image
    
    [out,[rows,cols]]=register_comp(scale,angle,move_x,move_y,interpolate,moving)
    
    loss_sum=0
    for i in range(rows):
        for j in range(cols):
            loss_sum=loss_sum + (fix[i,j] - out[i,j])**2
    
    return loss_sum


def optimize_comp(param,interpolate,images):
    x0=param
    res=minimize(loss_comp,x0,args=(interpolate,images,),method='Nelder-Mead')
    
    [scale,angle,move_x,move_y]=res.x
    [fix,moving]=images
    [out,shape]=register_comp(scale,angle,move_x,move_y,interpolate,moving)
    loss = loss_comp(res.x,1,images)
    return [res.x,loss]

def rle_encode(img):
    '''
    img: numpy array, 1 - mask, 0 - background
    Returns run length as string formated
    '''
    pixels = img.flatten()
    pixels = np.concatenate([[0], pixels, [0]])
    runs = np.where(pixels[1:] != pixels[:-1])[0] + 1
    runs[1::2] -= runs[::2]
    return ' '.join(str(x) for x in runs)
